```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Agent
    participant Tool as Tool
    participant ES as EventStream

    A->>Tool: execute(toolCallId, params, signal, onUpdate)
    Tool->>Tool: tool logic
    alt onUpdate provided & tool streams
        Tool->>A: onUpdate(partialResult)
        A->>ES: tool_execution_update (partialResult)
    end
    Tool-->>A: return { content, details }
    A->>ES: tool_execution_end (result, isError)
    A->>A: Create ToolResultMessage
    A->>ES: message_start (toolResult)
    A->>ES: message_end (toolResult)
```

---

**Notes**:
- Tool execution synchronous (await) but can stream via `onUpdate`.
- Agent captures errors: if `tool.execute()` throws, catch → result with error text, isError=true.
- Events: start (before execute), update (optional), end (after).
- ToolResultMessage then injected into context and emitted as message events.
